{
  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, we observed an increased level of MGMT promoter methylation in PTCC organoids compared to PT and PTN organoids (Fig. 3f), which indicates that PTCC organoids may respond better to TMZ treatment than PT and PTN organoids.",
    "Moreover, unsupervised cluster analysis demonstrates that different LEGOs can be categorized by human GBM DNA methylation classification probes 26 (Fig. 3g), indicating a human GBM-like methylation pattern in the LEGO model.",
    "It has been suggested that DNA methylation signatures can be used to determine the cell of origin in human cancers 28.",
    "Our analysis demonstrated that the DNA methylome is dynamic during tumor development and is dependent on the mutation spectrum.",
    "Therefore, it is crucial to use stable and mutationindependent DNA methylation patterns as tracers for cancer cell origin."
  ]
}